model possesses an additional symmetry resulting in the

conservation of magnetization along the z axis. For any
value of the anisotropy the model can be solved exactly ͑Lieb et al., 1961; Pfeuty, 1970; Barouch and McCoy, 1971͒. By ﬁrst applying the Jordan-Wigner transformation ck = ei␲͚jk=−11␴j+␴j−␴k− ͓with ␴± = ͑1 / 2͒͑␴x ± i␴y͔͒ the XY model can be transformed onto a free fermion Hamil-
